# Running Tests with BAI

BAI supports running tests with flexible filtering options for any package in your Thunderstorm project. This guide covers all test-related commands and parameters.

## Test Parameters

### Required Parameters

- **`--test`**: Enable test phase (required to run tests)

### Test Type Selection

- **`--test-type`**: Filter by test type (can specify multiple)
  - `pure`: Standard TypeScript tests using `ts-mocha` - pattern: `**/*.test.ts`
  - `firebase`: Tests with Firebase emulators - pattern: `**/*.test.firebase.ts`
  - `ui`: UI tests (not implemented yet)
  - `mobile`: Mobile tests (not implemented yet)

### Test Filtering

- **`--test-case`**: Run specific test cases (grep pattern matching test names)
  - Supports regex patterns
  - Multiple patterns can be combined with `|` (OR)
  - Example: `--test-case="Build|Deploy"` runs tests matching either pattern

- **`--test-file`**: Run specific test files (glob pattern)
  - Supports glob patterns like `**/*.test.ts`
  - Can specify multiple files

### Package Selection

- **`--use-packages`**: Select packages using regex pattern
  - Examples: `--use-package=build-and-install`, `--use-package=app-.*`, `--use-package=.*-frontend`
  - Only matching packages will have tests executed

### Other Useful Flags

- **`--no-build`**: Skip build phase (useful for test-only runs)
- **`--verbose`**: Enable verbose logging for detailed test output

## Test Types Explained

### Pure Tests (`--test-type=pure`)

Standard TypeScript tests that don't require external services:
- **Pattern**: `**/*.test.ts`
- **Command**: Uses `ts-mocha` with ESM support
- **Use case**: Unit tests, integration tests that don't need emulators

### Firebase Tests (`--test-type=firebase`)

Tests that require Firebase emulators:
- **Pattern**: `**/*.test.firebase.ts`
- **Command**: Wrapped in `firebase emulators:exec`
- **Use case**: Tests that need Firestore, Functions, or other Firebase services

## Examples

### Basic Test Commands

```bash
# Run pure tests in selected packages
bai --test --use-package=my-package --test-type=pure

# Run specific test case (grep pattern)
bai --test --test-case="My Test Case Name" --use-package=my-package --test-type=pure

# Run specific test file
bai --test --test-file="my-test.test.ts" --use-package=my-package --test-type=pure

# Skip build phase (useful when only running tests)
bai --test --use-package=my-package --test-type=pure -nb --verbose
```

### Run All Tests in a Package

```bash
# Run all pure tests in build-and-install package
bai --test --use-package=build-and-install --test-type=pure --verbose -nb
```

### Run Specific Test Case

```bash
# Run a specific test case by name
bai --test --test-case="Functions - Build and Push Container Image" --use-package=build-and-install --test-type=pure -nb

# Run multiple test cases (OR pattern)
bai --test --test-case="Build|Deploy" --use-package=my-package --test-type=pure -nb
```

### Run Specific Test File

```bash
# Run all tests in a specific file
bai --test --test-file="unit-build-push-image.test.ts" --use-package=build-and-install --test-type=pure -nb

# Run multiple test files using glob pattern
bai --test --test-file="**/unit-deploy*.test.ts" --use-package=build-and-install --test-type=pure -nb
```

### Debug Tests

```bash
# Run tests with debugger on port 9229
bai --test --use-package=my-package --test-type=pure -td=9229 -nb

# Then attach debugger in your IDE to localhost:9229
```

### Run Firebase Tests

```bash
# Run Firebase tests (requires Firebase emulators)
bai --test --use-package=my-package --test-type=firebase -nb
```

### Run Tests for Multiple Packages

```bash
# Run tests for all packages matching pattern
bai --test --use-package="app-.*" --test-type=pure -nb

# Run tests for all frontend packages
bai --test --use-package=".*-frontend" --test-type=pure -nb
```

### Common Workflows

```bash
# Quick test run (skip build, verbose output)
bai --test --use-package=my-package --test-type=pure -nb --verbose

# Run specific test case with verbose output
bai --test --test-case="My Test" --use-package=my-package --test-type=pure -nb --verbose

# Run all tests in package (with build)
bai --test --use-package=my-package --test-type=pure --verbose
```

## Troubleshooting

### Tests Not Found

If no tests are found:
- Check that test files match the pattern for the test type (`**/*.test.ts` for pure, `**/*.test.firebase.ts` for firebase)
- Verify the package matches the `--use-package` pattern
- Ensure test files are in `src/test/` directory

### Build Errors

If you get build errors when running tests:
- Fix build errors first, then run the specific tests that had failed

### Firebase Emulator Issues

If Firebase tests fail:
- Ensure Firebase emulators are properly configured
- Check that `firebase.json` and `.firebaserc` are set up correctly
- Verify emulator ports are available
